reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It’s not difficult to assemble this desk. There are a lot of parts and it can feel a bit tedious but it’s not hard per se. I was able to do the majority of it on my own but I was grateful to have a second set of hands to occasionally hold things in place. It took just under two hours but I also took a couple of breaks and was not in a rush. I think you could do it in less. The space is great and surprisingly organized given the lack of drawers. I wish there was one more drawer on your left where they put the top shelf. I’d say it was basically perfect if it had that. I’ll find a basket to stick there and I’ll be good to go. Hard to beat for the price. My husband calls is my command center. That’s honestly fairly accurate.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 2, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Happy with Desk!
reviews.reviewText: Absolutely love the desk, and it wasnt too expensive. While easy to put together as far as screws and it comes with Allen wrench etc. It was easy to assemble but the directions did not explain which side is the top or the front etc.. so put it together 3x before the holes lined up. I wish it had stickers saying the is front/back top/bottom because you can easily out it together and find out 25 steps later that they were wrong direction so now you have to undo it all to get the holes to line up. Directions were not detailed enough. However I finally got it together and it looks great, as shown in photo and get lots of compliments on the desk. I would definitely buy it again, just be very very careful with directions. Read it but look at photo to try and see what side is showing.

Reviewed in the United States on August 27, 2022
reviews.reviewText: After searching for a refurbished desk and not finding anything I liked, I decided to order this beauty. It was “delivered” by FedEx. They said it was delivered on August 7 however it wasn’t at either door nor surrounding apartment buildings. So, I contacted FedEx, they said they would contact that currier and have it delivered to the proper (initial) address, they never called with an update and when I called did not have an update. I decided to message the seller on the Amazon app and they always responded within the hour. They provided more information about FedEx than FedEx provided. They were considerate, timely, and sent me out a desk no questions asked. When the second desk was “delivered” FedEx still managed to drop it at the incorrect door but thankfully that tenant was nice enough to come tell us and help us bring it upstairs to our unit. Disappointed in FedEx, so incredibly pleased with the seller and their due diligence in alleviating this once annoying situation.It took my fiancé and I an hour and a half to assemble, great directions and extra buts and bolts which is always nice. The only confusing part was assembling the drawer but even that was somewhat self explanatory considering it’s the final step. I would definitely recommend this desk and the seller anytime! The desk is sturdy, sleek and just what I envisioned in my home office.
